summary:
President Trump called on allies including the UK, France, Japan, and South Korea to deploy warships to secure the Strait of Hormuz for oil tankers. This follows U.S. strikes yesterday on Iranian military sites on Kharg Island and warnings of oil infrastructure targets. Iran ordered evacuation of three UAE ports including Jebel Ali, Fujairah, and Khalifa. The developments affect global energy supplies passing through the strait, which carries 20% of world oil. Expanded naval operations by multiple nations are possible.

An Iran-backed militia launched a drone strike on the U.S. Embassy compound in Baghdad, the second such attack; the group claimed responsibility while the U.S. ordered citizens to leave Iraq, affecting American personnel there. U.S.-Israeli airstrikes hit a factory in Isfahan, killing 15 according to Iranian media and impacting nearby civilians. Iranian missile shrapnel burned cars and overturned one vehicle in a Tel Aviv district. An Israeli airstrike in Lebanon killed a civilian family; the IDF said it targeted Hezbollah sites, relatives denied any ties.

Israel allowed thousands of displaced Palestinians to cross a military zone into northern Gaza after a hostage release impasse ended, affecting 2 million residents and easing access temporarily. NATO deployed ships and aircraft after a second deep-sea communications cable was severed in the Baltic Sea, suspected as sabotage and disrupting European infrastructure. Russian airstrikes on the Kyiv region outskirts killed 4 civilians and wounded 15 after the U.S. paused Ukraine ceasefire talks due to the Iran conflict."}
